data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>()`. In MSTest v3+ it returns the cast object, so you can combine the type check and assignment:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

**Why this is better:**
- A wrong type gives a clear assertion failure instead of an `InvalidCastException`
- No separate null check needed — the assert handles it
- Returns the typed instance, so you can keep testing properties
